u / \mathrm{GHz}ight)^{-3}$, $	au$ represents the pulse broadening (i.e., scattering) timescale at 1\,GHz, scaled to 1.4\,GHz according to a scattering index $\alpha$ as $	au \propto 
u^{-\alpha}$, $\Theta(t)$ is the Heaviside unit step function, and $\ast$ symbolizes a convolution. We fixed the scattering index at $\alpha\!=\!4$, as implied by the functional form of Eq.~ef{eq:expgauss}
